ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Comments about assessment
Form used/assessment name
Notes: e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version

ElementDescription: Trial number
Indicates whether they were choosing for themselves, their friend, or a stranger
Monetary amount for gain option
Monetary amount for loss option
Monetary amount for certain option
If gamble is chosen, whether the predetermined outcome is a win or loss
If the gamble is chosen, the amount that is won or lost at given outcome
Notes: The amount that is won or lost at given outcome

ElementDescription: Button Pressed
Notes: 1= Chose Gamble; 6= Chose Certain; 999= Missed Trial

ElementDescription: Interstimulus interval (ISI) duration and units
Inter trial interval (ITI) duration and units
Block
Reaction Time
How did you feel while losing money for (friend)?
How did you feel while winning money for (friend)?
How did you feel while losing money for (stranger)?
How did you feel while winning money for (stranger)?
How did you feel while losing money for (self)?
How did you feel while winning money for (self)?
Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime
